main event: On April 11, 1955, a ground-visual UFO sighting was reported over the Atlantic Ocean. The object was described as circular, bluish silver, larger than the moon, and emitted no sound.
interesting points: The UFO sighting lasted for 50 seconds.
The object appeared larger than the moon and emitted a brilliant blue-green light.
The report card indicates that there were photos taken of the sighting.
The document suggests that there was uncertainty about the nature of the object, with possibilities ranging from balloons to aircraft to meteors.
Another sighting on March 9, 1955, described an object emitting a brilliant blue-green light and appearing to be a round saucer-like object.
sighted object: circular, bluish silver object larger than the moon
